  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      International recommendations (ACR,EULAR) emphasize physical exercise and weight loss for
      patients suffering from knee osteoarthritis. Nevertheless, number of patients receiving
      advices for these 2 points still low. This study evaluates the impact of a standardized
      medical intervention (patient education, weight reduction and physical exercise) in knee
      osteoarthritis patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
